comment: Brooks (IND) maintains legal guarding position on Johnson (MIA) and does not affect his FOM off ball.
Turner (IND) legally contests Teague's (IND) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
George (IND) sets the screen on Johnson (MIA) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Teague (IND) reaches in on the drive to the basket by Johnson (MIA) and any contact is incidental.
Turner (IND) obtains a legal guarding position and jumps vertically on the driving shot attempt by Johnson (MIA).
Prior to the inbound pass, Dragic (MIA) makes marginal contact with Young (IND).
[Observable in enhanced video] Johnson (MIA) moves his pivot foot on the spin move.
Whiteside (MIA) is in the paint without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.
Richardson (MIA) maintains legal guarding position on the drive to the basket by George (IND).
Richardson (MIA) and George (IND) make incidental contact with one another during rebounding.
Brooks (IND) makes contact with Whiteside (MIA) just prior to Richardson (MIA) catching the pass.
Richardson (MIA) gathers the ball and takes the legal two steps.
Turner (IND) commits a take foul on Whiteside (MIA).
Richardson (MIA) makes incidental contact with George (IND) that does not affect his SQBR.
